name: ✨𝕴𝖑𝖑𝖚𝖘𝖙𝖗𝖔 - 1st Edition - (Photoreal Fantasy Model)✨
description:
NOW OVER 1400 downloads!❤️
per sacrificium purificant

This model is the next evolution of a pure-photorealistic fantasy model. Capable of creating any character & any setting you can feasibly conceive!

It's the most detailed & thoroughly made model I've released as of yet & I spent tireless nights fine-tuning this to be the most epic model I could manage. I spent roughly a month generating examples and running it through its paces. It's also capable of using most LORA's quite effectively so you should be able to create whatever you like.

ALL THE MAIN EXAMPLES ARE 1:1 FOLLOWING MY INSTRUCTIONS YOU SHOULD BE ABLE TO REPLICATE THEM EASILY!

This model can do pretty much any style fantasy art at a very high level. The main concepts:

✔️ fantasy art (retro & modern)
✔️ characters / rpg characters
✔️ photorealistic / realistic
✔️ analog style
✔️ surrealism
✔️ oil painting
✔️ concept art
✔️ cinematic

(all of the above list can & should be used as triggers and weights)

It knows most common D&D races and it will produce some interesting great results when prompted correctly. (It has some minor issues with complicated races such as dragonborn & tieflings, etc. but you should be able to use a LORA to render these effectively. <3)

How to use

There is no embedded VAE but it was designed to be used with this:

☞ vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned.ckpt

I also recommend using the following negatives:

EasyNegative or EasyNegativeV2 (The all around catch all. Always good in a bind)
badhandv4_anime (absolutely your go to neg for anime hands)
bad-hands-5 (good for the more realistic images but will not work amazingly for anime)
bad-artist \ bad-artist-anime (I’ve had good and bad luck)
bad_prompt \ bad_prompt_version2 (works very good sometimes)
(I typically use (bad-hands-5) & (bandhandv4_anime) at the same time to cover all bases.)


(Here are some example settings for you to start with, but please keep in mind YMMV!)

Steps: 30 = Sweet Spot / 10-150
Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras, DPM++ SDE Karras, Euler A, DDIM,
CFG scale: 4-11.5 = Sweet Spot / 4.5-15
Size: 512x768, 768x512, 640x840, 840x640, 600x896, 896x600, (any size)
Clip skip: 1
Hires Fix: Enabled
Upscale by: 1.5-2
Hires Steps: Equal to Half or Exact the exact amount of Steps (or higher)
Upscaler: Remacri Upscaler, Lollypop Upscaler, 4x_NMKD_DigArt_10k|
( I use DigArt 10k almost exclusively with everything except for 2D illustration & animation )
